 but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger de Conyers was born about 1150, in Clifford, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Roger Conyers III, was 16 and his mother, Albreda of norton, was 11. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Roger de Conyers."},"et":{"about 1150–":"umbes 1150–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1160–1238":"1160–1238","1162–1195":"1162–1195","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1156–Female":"1156–Surnud","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1135–1174":"1135–1174","1140–1189":"1140–1189","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1190":"1190","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1165":"1165","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","1195":"1195","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1238":"1238","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1156":"1156","Galfred, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1150–":"noin 1150–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1160–1238":"1160–1238","1162–1195":"1162–1195","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1156–Female":"1156–Kuollut","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1135–1174":"1135–1174","1140–1189":"1140–1189","about 1150":"noin 1150","1190":"1190","about 1190":"noin 1190","1165":"1165","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","1195":"1195","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1238":"1238","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1156":"1156","Galfred, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1150–":"environ 1150–Décédé","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1160–1238":"1160–1238","1162–1195":"1162–1195","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1156–Female":"1156–Décédée","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1135–1174":"1135–1174"